ead Negev doctrine" used by Israel to dispossess and forcefully displace Bedouin inhabitants in order to Judaize the region. The authors reveal that through manipulative use of Ottoman, British and Israeli laws, the state has constructed its own version ofterra nullius. Yet, the indigenous property and settlement system still functions, creating an ongoing resistance to the Jewish state.Emptied Lands critically examines several key land claims, court rulings, planning policies, and development strategies, offering alternative local, regional, and international routes for justice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aBedouinsxLand tenurezIsraelzNegev. 0aBedouinsxLegal status, laws, etczIsraelzNegev. 0aBedouinsxLegal status, laws, etc.zIsraelzNegev. 0aLand tenurexLaw and legislationzIsraelzNegev. 4aBedouins. 4aBritish Mandate. 4aDead (Mewat) Land. 4aDead Negev Doctrine. 4aInternal Colonialism. 4aIsrael. 4aNegev. 4aOttoman. 4aPalestine. 4aTerra Nullius. 7aLAW / Indigenous Peoples.2bisacsh1 aAmara, Ahmad, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aYiftachel, Oren, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311070368940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781503604582zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503604582423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503604582.jpg  a978-3-11-070368-9  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles